{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b00e7271-9162-4317-ab0a-c2b4bbb1bf07","content":"Here's what I found in `my_app/`:\n\n### Untestable Static Dependencies\n\n| File | Line | Call | Risk |\n|------|------|------|------|\n| `views.py` | 3 | `datetime.now()` | 🔴 Non-deterministic time |\n\n**1 static call site found** in 1 file.\n\n### Why it's a problem\n`datetime.now()` makes the view's output depend on wall-clock time, so you can't write a reliable assertion against the returned `time` context variable.\n\n### Recommended fix (Python/Django)\nUse Django's `django.utils.timezone.now` and mock it in tests with [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) or `unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\n# views.py\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\n```python\n# tests.py — deterministic test\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom django.test import TestCase\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nclass IndexViewTest(TestCase):\n    @patch('my_app.views.timezone.now',\n           return_value=datetime(2026, 1, 1))\n    def test_index_time(self, mock_now):\n        response = self.client.get('/')\n        self.assertEqual(response.context['time'],\n                         datetime(2026, 1, 1))\n```\n\nThis is a small project with only one call site — a quick fix! Want me to apply the change?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0f3dc85e-3c52-4688-a2e1-7302207765ec","outputTokens":387,"requestId":"3401:391BC6:96EAD:B81BB:69F413A7"},"id":"c87f557c-acd5-4a77-8926-62d55674666f","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:45:03.591Z","parentId":"d0c7ab1d-2e56-4fcf-ae0c-3dba6a7645dd"}
